@node "eInt" "X-bEnCh :: Introduction"
  @{b}Introduction:
  ------------@{ub}

  Hi there! My name is Jim Neray and i come from France.
  X-bEnCh is one of my projects. I have this project in mind from
  many years but the dev only really start in the summer 2010.

  The first main goal of X-bEnCh was to create a cool games/tools
  launcher who can remind to every one the feeling of the cracktros
  of our olds 80's/90's Amiga games. After that the project grow up
  to a new level;

  Now the idea is that X-bEnCh can be used from the Workbench or, if
  you want to, X-bEnCh can totally replace your Workbench. Actually
  X-bEnCh can handle up to 7 launching listings (Games, Demos, ...)
  of many types (whdload, .exe, script system or manuals listings).
  It has an integreted evolved CLI, a dirs/files manager and a system
  friendly setup panel. All that is working with up to 128 colors on
  screen with OCS/ECS and 272 colors with AGA capable setup.

  The team behind X-bEnCh is: Jim (Me!) ... Coding
                              Leon ........ Art Drawing
                              WodK ........ 3D Rendering
                              Curt Cool ... Sound Designer


  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "eReq" "X-bEnCh :: Requirements"
  @{b}Requirements:
  ------------@{ub}

  X-bEnCh can be launched by any Amiga Computer. No big 68060/100Mhz
  or AGA/CGX is needed. But remember that whdload use more ram than
  the originals games so more you've ram better it is.

  Minimum setup : Any Amiga with a harddrive or any other mass storage.
  Average setup : 2Mb of chipram, 4Mb of fastram, harddrive.
  Perfect setup : 68020+, 2Mb of chipram, 8+Mb of fastram.

  Additionaly you need this 3 commands in your c drawer:	  
  list, sort, wait
  
  You also (indeed) need to have Whdload installed.
  
 
  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

