@node "eIns" "X-bEnCh :: Installation"
  @{b}Installation:
  ------------@{ub}

  To install X-bEnCh simply use the Xinstaller. Use the "P" button
  to choose the Path where you want to install the Xbench Drawer.
  If an old release was installed your setup files will be used.
  
  You can also add Xbench to your startup-sequence. To do so, REPLACE
  the line c:loadwb by this two lines:

     @{i}cd yourhardrive:yourxbenchpath
     execute xbench.exe@{ui}

  Then when you start your Amiga X-bEnCh will load automaticaly on
  startup but, if you press the "DEL" key when loading, X-bEnCh'll
  not start. Your workbench will be started instead. You can change
  this in the "Startup" tab in the @{" Setup " Link "eSUs"} to make
  the Workbench loaded as default and X-bEnCh loaded if you press
  the "DEL" Key.


  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode


@node "eReg" "X-bEnCh :: How to register"
  @{b}How to register:
  ----------------@{ub}
  
  I spend a large amount of time every month for X-bEnCh so, if you
  like it please consider registering yourself.
  
  X-bEnCh is Donationware. A donation of 10 euros (15 US$) is recommanded.
  
  To get a registered keyfile you can simply use the "Donate" button on my
  website (www.jimneray.com) and then send me a mail at jimneray@gmail.com
  with your Name and your First Name. I will then send you your registered
  X-bEnCh keyfile.
  
  Please note that some free keys are available if you've worked on
  the X-bEnCh project for gfx, msx or in exchange of a registration
  key of one of your Amiga software.
  
  The unregistereds users has no special limitation except the PleaseReg
  screen on Startup. Registered users will have access to all the privates
  internals releases.
  
  
  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "eOUs" "X-bEnCh :: Overall Usage"
  @{b}Overall Usage:
  -------------@{ub}

  Except for the Setup, X-bEnCh can be controled either with the
  keyboard or with a joystick plugged in the 2nd Game port.

  The Setup can be controled with the mouse or with a joystick if
  you use the Joy2Mouse option in the setup.
  
  The Xpl0rer can only be controled with a mouse.


  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "eSUs" "X-bEnCh :: Setup Usage"
  @{b}Setup Usage:
  -----------@{ub}

  On the left of the "X-bEnCh Setup Panel" you've got many navigation Tabs,
  simply use them to navigate in the setup.


  > Startup Tab <
  
  Here you can setup how X-bEnch will start.
  
  "Boot To"     : With this button you can choose where X-bEnch will be
                  after the loading screen (Menu, Launcher, cLi, ...).

  "Press DEL"   : With this switch you can choose if X-bench or Workbench
                  is loaded by default. Very usefull if you replace the
                  loadwb command in your startup-sequence with xbench.
                  If you select X-bEnch, Xbench will be loaded by default
                  but if you press the "DEL" key during the startup this
                  will abord the X-bEnch loading and start the Workbench
                  instead.
                  If you select Workbench, the Workbench'll be loaded by
                  default but if you press the "DEL" key during the startup
                  this'll abord the Workbench loading and start X-bEnch
                  instead.
                  
  "LoadWB Arg"  : Here you can add some args to be used when loadwb is
                  executed by xbench, for example when you press the "DEL"
                  key to abord the X-bEnch loading.
                                    
  "Boot Fade"   : Use this button to switch On/Off the fading effect on
                  the Workbench screen when X-bEnch is starting.

  "StartScript" : Here you can select an AmigaDos script to execute before
                  starting X-bEnCh (to switch off some app/hack that may
                  disturb X-bEnCh like copper background hack for example).
  
  "ExitScript"  : Here you can select an AmigaDos script to execute after
                  leaving X-bEnCh (to switch on the app/hack previously
                  switched off with a StartScript for example).
  
  "Regscreen"   : Registered users can switch On/Off the regscreen with
                  there name/serial number with this switch.
                  
                  
  > My System Tab <
  
  This part is done to set your computer parts more than Xbench himself.
  
  "CD Mode"     : Switch this option "ON" if you want to create an Amiga
                  CD compilation for CD32 or CDTV. Beware ! You must setup
                  all your compilation before using this switch. Never use
                  it before all is ok, it's clearly the very last thing you
                  must do before burning a cd.

  "AudioMode"   : Use the (default) New Replay Routine for the best result.
                  If this mode fail switch back to the Old Replay Routine. 

  "DebugMode"   : If switched "On" this option will create a log file in
                  the xbench directory named "xbench.log". Please use this
                  option and send me this log file with your bug reports.
                  Please note that you can force the debug mode even if
                  this option is switched to "Off" by pressing the "d" key
                  when X-bench is loading.
                        
  "TurboMode"   : If "On" all the security checks and controls will NOT be
                  dones. This will be faster but take care to use this 
                  option only after having checked that all is ok (missing
                  files, unworking slaves, bad installs, ...). If something
                  goes wrong simply switch back this option to "Off" and
                  check from where come your issue.
                                     
  "SetClock"    : Here you can set the system date and time. Simply use the
  		  "+" and "-" buttons to set up your RTC (Real Time Clock).                  


  > Main Menu <
  
  Here are the Main menu options.
  
  "Music"       : Simply switch On/Off the music of the Main menu.
  
  "Starfield"   : Again, simply switch On/Off the RotoStarfield effect.

  "Exitto"      : With this switch you can choose where to go when choosing
                  "Exit" in the main menu. You have 3 choice: "Nowhere" to
                  simply leave, "LoadWB" to loadwb (with args if specified
                  in "Setup/Startup") after leaving X-bEnCh or "Reboot" to
                  ... Reboot your migy :)
    
                      
  > Launchers Tab <

  Here you can setup all the launcher parts. On the left you've got the six
  main setup parts of each of your 6 launching lists. Each of them have 5
  interesting items:

  "List Type"   : This button switch between all the available listings
                  types. You can choose between, Disabled, Manual, WhdLoad
                  and .Exe.
                  If you choose "Manual", you've to edit by yourself the
                  listing in the "xb:prefs/" dir. The listing is named
                  "list1" for the first list, "list2" for the 2nd list, ...
                  If you choose WhdLoad or .Exe type, all is automatised.
                  If you choose Disabled, the listing is simply.. disabled!

  "List Name"   : Here you can choose the name of your listing.

  "Path to scan": Simply enter the path that you want to scan here. The "P"
                  button open a rquester to choose a path. Usefull if you
                  don't have any keyboard on your game machine.

  "Update!"     : Clic here when all is finished to start the autoscan of
                  your hard drive. This will work for the whdload ".slave"
                  and the ".exe". Beware, the scan can take a long time
                  cause X-bEnCh will recursively scan an unlimited sublevels
                  of dirs so be patient.

  On the right you've got the "Launchers Options".
  
  "MEgaRam"     : Here you can activate or not the "MegaRam" option to try
                  to gain extra ram before launching a game. This will help
                  you to gain from 30/40kb of ram to many more.
  
  "MUsic"       : Switch On/Off the music in the Launcher & the loader.
  
  "TopList"     : Activate the Top List opening when you start the launcher.
  		  The Top List will be the first list loaded and is a bestof
  		  all your listings in a single list. You can use the "F7"
  		  key to go to the Top List at any time.

  "CD32Pad"     : If switched to "On" the launcher will use a 7 buttons pad
                  instead of a basic 1/2 buttons one.                  

  
  > WHDLoad <

  21 Buttons are implemented here to setup 23 Tooltypes. The tooltypes that
  will be setuped here will be used when launching a .slave if no tooltypes
  can be found in a .info file.
  
  "ShowWhdloadRequester" : If "YES" the whdload requester will be showed
                           every time that you start a whdload slave file.
                           You will've 10s to choose your options before
                           the screen fall to black and your slave start.
                           If "No" the screen will stay black and your
                           whdload slave will start immediately except if
                           some options must be choosed for this slave.
                           In this case you'll have 10s to choose your
                           options before the screen fall to black and
                           your whdload slave start.
                           
                           
  > Xpl0rer <
  
  Not yet implemented.
  
  
  > c.L.i <
  
  Here you can change the options of the X-bEnch shell.
  
  "Bg Colour"   : Change the background color.
  "Colour 1"    : Change the color of the text.
  "Colour 2"    : Change the highlight color.
  
  
  > Setup <
  
  Here you can ... setup the setup ... Yes really. :)
  
  "Music"       : Switch On/Off the music in the setup panel.
  "Joy2Mouse"   : If "On" you can use a joypad/stick pluged in the mouseport
                  to control the setup. Really usefull for CD32/CDTV with
                  no mouse pluged.
                  
                  
  > Exit Setup Tab <

  Simply clic on the "Exit Setup" tab to go back to the main menu.


  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "eLUs" "X-bEnCh :: Launcher Usage"
  @{b}Launcher Usage:
  --------------@{ub}

  - Move Up or Down with the arrow keys or with your pad in joy port 2 to
    go up or down in a listing.
  - Move Left or right with the arrow keys or with your pad in joy port 2
    to switch pages in the launcher.
  - Launch the selected entry with Fire button 1, "Return", "Enter"
    or "Space" Key. Please note that a short push on the fire button 1 will
    use the default tooltypes find with your whdload file. A long push will
    force the use of the tooltypes that you have set in the whdload pannel
    in th the xbench setup. The screen will flash in green in this case.
  - Fastly jump where you want with the "A" to "Z" and "0" to "9" Keys.
  - Switch from a listing to another with the "Tab" Key or with a short
    pressure on the Fire button 2.
  - You can also use the F1 to F6 key to jump to the list 1 to list 6.
  - You can use the F7 key to jump to the Top List.
  - Return to main menu screen with the "Esc" Key or with a long pressure
    on the Fire button 2.
  - If you want to jump to a game name, you can simply use the Xbench search
    engine. To do so, simply use your keyboard and enter the name of the 
    game that you want and xbench will bring you in real time to the exact
    name of the game of your choice.

    
  For CD32 Pad only:
  
  - Move up or down to go up or down in the actual listing.
  - Move left or right to switch pages in the actual listing.
  - Press Red to start the selected entry with detected tooltypes.
  - Press green to force the selected entry to start with your tooltypes.
  - Press blue to switch between listings.
  - Press yellow to go back to the Main Menu.
  - Press Forward to jump to the next letter (0>9/A>Z).
  - Press rewind to jump to the previous letter (Z>A/9>0).


  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "eXUs" "X-bEnCh :: Xpl0rer Usage"
  @{b}Xpl0rer Usage:
  -------------@{ub}
  
  Simply use your mouse to control this Files/Dirs manager. Xpl0rer is
  really new and this part of the X-bEnCh guide will be updated as soon
  as possible with a future release.
  
  
  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "eCUs" "X-bEnCh :: cLi Usage"
  @{b}cLi Usage:
  ---------@{ub}

  The X-bEnCh cLi simply work as like as a workbench cli but with some
  extra commands. If you don't know what to do after you've launched the
  cLi, simply type: "endcli" and push the enter or return key.

  Use the command "help" to have a short help text and the list of the
  extra X-bEnCh cLi commands that are installed in your X-bEnCh.


  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "eBug" "X-bEnCh :: Bugs"
  @{b}Known Bugs & Bugs Reports:
  -------------------------@{ub}

  The only know bug at this time is the one that freeze the countdown of
  the reg screen at 501. It has been reported with a 4k with Appolo040
  and a custom rom. If you have this bug too please contact me.

  You can Bug Report me at: jimneray@gmail.com

  Please remember to explain me how to reproduce your bug and to give me a
  description of your Amiga and System setup. If possible create and send
  me an xbench.log (created by using the "d" key when xbench is loading).


  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "eFaq" "X-bEnCh :: FAQ"
  @{b}Frequently Asked Questions:
  --------------------------@{ub}
  
  @{b}Q:@{ub} When i try to start a game the screen double flash in blue
     but nothing happens. Why ?
  @{b}A:@{ub} The double blue flash notify you that the game that you are
     trying to launch doesn't exist in your hard disc. Simply update your
     listing in the setup if some files have been deleted or added.
     
  @{b}Q:@{ub} When i try to launch X-bEnCh.exe an alert on the screen
     tell me that some files are missing. Why ?
  @{b}A:@{ub} It seem that your xb archive has been badly extracted. Try
     to extract it again with the all files option activated.

  @{b}Q:@{ub} X-bEnCh seem to start but i can't start the Setup or/and the
     Launcher. What's the problem ?
  @{b}A:@{ub} It seem that you have corrupted setup files or too old ones,
     probably because you have extracted the new xbench archive over
     an old installation of xbench. Start the X-bEnCh cLi and use the
     "resetxset" command to delete all your listings and clean up all
     your setup files. After that, all should be ok.

  @{b}Q:@{ub} Whith some games, the screen fall to black after the loading
     screen and nothing happen. Why ?
  @{b}A:@{ub} Some .slave don't work if you don't have a registered version
     of WhdLoad (BAT2 for exemple). Switch the WhdLoadReq "ON" in the setup
     to see what really happens. PLEASE NOTE that this issue should no more
     happen from the X-bEnCh 0.94F release. If it does please contact me.

  @{b}Q:@{ub} How can i use script instead of .slave or .exe ?
  @{b}A:@{ub} It's really easy. Simply create a script with a name ending
     with .xbs and put it in the drawer of your .slave or .exe. If
     X-bEnCh find a .xbs in a drawer, it'll execute it instead of
     anything.


  @{" Back to Main Menu " Link "Main"}
@endnode

